node.text: Follow along as Jamie show us how to make a delicious, nutritious spin on classic chips and dip. Here's the recipe! http://www.cookinglight.com/eating-smart/recipe-makeovers/lower-calorie-french-onion-dip

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on August 03, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and food.

node.text: Cooked greens and crispy potatoes are great as a base for a skillet hash, but why not try something new? Pile into lightly charred corn tortillas, and top with vibrant toppings such as fresh cilantro and radishes to turn a one-note leftover into a tasty, satisfying main. Click the link in our bio for the recipe!  #tacotuesday 🌮🌮

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on August 03, 2021.

node.text: Simple yet radically sophisticated, this dish comes together in less than 30 minutes. Plus, eating salmon twice a week provides major heart-protective benefits according to the American Heart Association. ❤️🎣 Click the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 30, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: If there were a gut health Olympics, this salad would take home the gold medal. Not only does it include healthy probiotics courtesy of the kefir dressing, it’s also full of healthy prebiotics—fiber-full vegetables that your gut bacteria feasts on. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🥇

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 30, 2021. May be an image of fruit.

node.text: We're giving the one-cup summer dessert an upgrade with a bit of Hawaiian flair. The result? A tropical dessert that fits the clean eating bill and uses just 5 ingredients. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 29, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: The sweet potato keeps its superfood status in this healthy recipe for oven fries. A sprinkling of grated orange peel adds a zesty note. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 29, 2021. May be an image of strawberry.

node.text: This is a tastier version of those strawberry shortcake bars from the ice cream truck. The crust is salty, buttery, and slightly tart—a perfect crunchy match to the creamy and sweet white chocolate filling. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍰

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 28, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Upgrade your pickle game with these crunchy and zesty fast-fix pickles. Great for topping tacos, stir fries, salads, or snazzing up an appetizer board, these crunchy pickles deliver a pop of flavor to everyday dishes. Click the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: Refreshing the coconut flakes in a bit of coconut oil gives them a lovely sheen and makes the salad incredibly aromatic. The lime juice and zest bring the whole thing together. Click the link in our bio for the recipe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 28, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This loaded veggie bowl gets a touch of smoke from the chili-spiced sweet potatoes and roasted bell pepper and plenty of zing from fresh lime. Chili powder and lime also give toasted almonds an addictive crust. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! 🍠🌶️

node.text: Simple, bright, and balanced, this salad pairs perfectly with grilled fish or chicken. Click the link in our bio for the recipe: Golden Beet Salad with Avocado and Feta 🥗

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cooking Light on July 27, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: These tacos are a perfect blend of Mexican street corn (also called elote) and quick-cooking skirt steak. If you have frozen corn, blister the kernels in a skillet over high heat first. Click the link in our bio for the recipe! #tacotuesday 🌮🌮🌮

node.text: Infused with a rich corn broth, this corn- and mushroom-studded risotto is a stellar way to celebrate the season’s harvest. Feel free to sub in your favorite mushrooms; steer clear of large portobellos—their dark gills will discolor the finished dish. Click the link in our bio for the recipe!
